Usage: editAddTrimMetal [-help] [-layer <string>] -location {x y}
                        [-mask <integer>] [-snap_to_end]

-help               # Prints out the command usage
-layer <string>     # Specifies the layer to add trim metal.The layer name
                    # should be a routing layer which be defined in the LEF
                    # file. (string, optional)
-location {x y}     # Specify proximate location of trimMetal, tool may adjust
                    # automatically to closest location which is best for the
                    # trimMetal (point, required)
-mask <integer>     # Specify the mask of trim metal (int, optional)
-snap_to_end        # Specify to snap trimMetal to closest end of selected pin
                    # or wire (bool, optional)